1 Section 2. Section 7-32-201, MCA, is amended to read:
2 "7-32-201. Definitions. As used in this part, the following definitions apply:
3 (1) "Auxiliary officer" means an unsworn, part-time, volunteer member of a law enforcement
4 agency who may perform but is not limited to the performance of such functions as civil defense, search and
5 rescue, office duties, crowd and traffic control, and crime prevention activities.
6 (2) "Council" means the Montana public safety officer standards and training council established in
7 2-15-2029.
8 (3) "General law enforcement duties" means patrol operations performed for detection, prevention,
9 and suppression of crime and the enforcement of criminal and traffic codes of this state and its local
10 governments.
11 (4) "Law enforcement agency" means a law enforcement service provided directly by a local
12 government.
13 (5) "Law enforcement officer" means a sworn, full-time, employed member of a law enforcement
14 agency who is a peace officer, as defined in 46-1-202, and has arrest authority, as described in 46-6-210.
15 (6) "Reserve officer" means a sworn, part-time, volunteer member of a law enforcement agency or
16 a part-time, paid member of a law enforcement agency serving as a court officer as provided in 3-6-303. The
17 volunteer member or the part-time paid member is a peace officer, as defined in 46-1-202, and has arrest
18 authority, as described in 46-6-210, only when authorized to perform these functions as a representative of the
19 law enforcement agency.
20 (7) "Special services officer" means an unsworn, full-time or part-time, volunteer or paid member of
21 a law enforcement agency who may perform functions, other than general law enforcement duties, that require
22 specialized skills, training, and qualifications, who may be required to train with a firearm, and who may carry a
23 firearm while on assigned duty as provided in 7-32-239."
24 - END -
